    - title: 
      content: "Salt is good for seasoning. But if it loses its flavor, how do you
        make it salty again? You must have the qualities of salt among yourselves
        and live in peace with each other.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Discussion about Divorce and Marriage
      content: 'Then Jesus left Capernaum and went down to the region of Judea and
        into the area east of the Jordan River. Once again crowds gathered around
        him, and as usual he was teaching them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Some Pharisees came and tried to trap him with this question: \u201CShould
        a man be allowed to divorce his wife?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus answered them with a question: \n\t\u201CWhat did Moses say
        in the law about divorce?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWell, he permitted it,\u201D they replied. \u201CHe said a
        man can give his wife a written notice of divorce and send her away.\u201D[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: See Deut 24:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus responded, \n\t\u201CHe wrote this commandment only as
        a concession to your hard hearts.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But \u2018God made them male and female\u2019[COMMENT[0]]  \n\tfrom
        the beginning of creation.  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: Gen 1:27; 5:2.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018This explains why a man leaves his father and mother and is
        joined to his wife,[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts do not include '
          body: and is joined to his wife.
    - title: 
      content: "and the two are united into one.\u2019[COMMENT[0]]  \n\tSince they
        are no longer two but one,  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:7-8 '
        contents:
        - ft: Gen 2:24.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "let no one split apart what God has joined together.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Later, when he was alone with his disciples in the house, they brought
        up the subject again. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He told them, \n\t\u201CWhoever divorces his wife and marries someone
        else commits adultery against her.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if a woman divorces her husband and marries someone else, she
        commits adultery.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Blesses the Children
      content: 'One day some parents brought their children to Jesus so he could
        touch and bless them. But the disciples scolded the parents for bothering
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Jesus saw what was happening, he was angry with his disciples.
        He said to them, \n\t\u201CLet the children come to me. Don\u2019t stop them!
        For the Kingdom of God belongs to those who are like these children.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I tell you the truth, anyone who doesn\u2019t receive the Kingdom
        of God like a child will never enter it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then he took the children in his arms and placed his hands on their
        heads and blessed them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Rich Man
      content: "As Jesus was starting out on his way to Jerusalem, a man came running
        up to him, knelt down, and asked, \u201CGood Teacher, what must I do to inherit
        eternal life?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CWhy do you call me good?\u201D \n\tJesus asked. \n\t\u201COnly
        God is truly good.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But to answer your question, you know the commandments: \u2018You
        must not murder. You must not commit adultery. You must not steal. You must
        not testify falsely. You must not cheat anyone. Honor your father and mother.\u2019[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: Exod 20:12-16; Deut 5:16-20.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTeacher,\u201D the man replied, \u201CI\u2019ve obeyed all
        these commandments since I was young.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Looking at the man, Jesus felt genuine love for him. \n\t\u201CThere
        is still one thing you haven\u2019t done,\u201D \n\the told him. \n\t\u201CGo
        and sell all your possessions and give the money to the poor, and you will
        have treasure in heaven. Then come, follow me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At this the man\u2019s face fell, and he went away sad, for he had
        many possessions.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus looked around and said to his disciples, \n\t\u201CHow hard
        it is for the rich to enter the Kingdom of God!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This amazed them. But Jesus said again, \n\t\u201CDear children,
        it is very hard[COMMENT[0]]  \n\tto enter the Kingdom of God.  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:24 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts read '
          body: very hard for those who trust in riches.
    - title: 
      content: "In fact, it is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle
        than for a rich person to enter the Kingdom of God!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The disciples were astounded. \u201CThen who in the world can be
        saved?\u201D they asked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus looked at them intently and said, \n\t\u201CHumanly speaking,
        it is impossible. But not with God. Everything is possible with God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Peter began to speak up. \u201CWe\u2019ve given up everything
        to follow you,\u201D he said.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CYes,\u201D \n\tJesus replied, \n\t\u201Cand I assure
        you that everyone who has given up house or brothers or sisters or mother
        or father or children or property, for my sake and for the Good News,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "will receive now in return a hundred times as many houses, brothers,
        sisters, mothers, children, and property\u2014along with persecution. And
        in the world to come that person will have eternal life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But many who are the greatest now will be least important then, and
        those who seem least important now will be the greatest then.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:31 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: But many who are first will be last; and the last, first.
    - title: Jesus Again Predicts His Death
      content: 'They were now on the way up to Jerusalem, and Jesus was walking ahead
        of them. The disciples were filled with awe, and the people following behind
        were overwhelmed with fear. Taking the twelve disciples aside, Jesus once
        more began to describe everything that was about to happen to him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen,\u201D \n\the said, \n\t\u201Cwe\u2019re going up to
        Jerusalem, where the Son of Man[COMMENT[0]]  \n\twill be betrayed to the
        leading priests and the teachers of religious law. They will sentence him
        to die and hand him over to the Romans.[COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:33a '
        contents:
        - ft: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
          body: 
      - number: '10:33b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: the Gentiles.
    - title: 
      content: "They will mock him, spit on him, flog him with a whip, and kill him,
        but after three days he will rise again.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Teaches about Serving Others
      content: "Then James and John, the sons of Zebedee, came over and spoke to
        him. \u201CTeacher,\u201D they said, \u201Cwe want you to do us a favor.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CWhat is your request?\u201D \n\the asked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They replied, \u201CWhen you sit on your glorious throne, we want
        to sit in places of honor next to you, one on your right and the other on
        your left.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus said to them, \n\t\u201CYou don\u2019t know what you are
        asking! Are you able to drink from the bitter cup of suffering I am about
        to drink? Are you able to be baptized with the baptism of suffering I must
        be baptized with?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COh yes,\u201D they replied, \u201Cwe are able!\u201D\n\tThen
        Jesus told them, \n\t\u201CYou will indeed drink from my bitter cup and be
        baptized with my baptism of suffering.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I have no right to say who will sit on my right or my left. God
        has prepared those places for the ones he has chosen.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the ten other disciples heard what James and John had asked,
        they were indignant. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Jesus called them together and said, \n\t\u201CYou know that the
        rulers in this world lord it over their people, and officials flaunt their
        authority over those under them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But among you it will be different. Whoever wants to be a leader
        among you must be your servant,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and whoever wants to be first among you must be the slave of everyone
        else.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For even the Son of Man came not to be served but to serve others
        and to give his life as a ransom for many.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Heals Blind Bartimaeus
      content: 'Then they reached Jericho, and as Jesus and his disciples left town,
        a large crowd followed him. A blind beggar named Bartimaeus (son of Timaeus)
        was sitting beside the road. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Bartimaeus heard that Jesus of Nazareth was nearby, he began
        to shout, \u201CJesus, Son of David, have mercy on me!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBe quiet!\u201D many of the people yelled at him.\n\tBut he
        only shouted louder, \u201CSon of David, have mercy on me!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Jesus heard him, he stopped and said, \n\t\u201CTell him to
        come here.\u201D\n\tSo they called the blind man. \u201CCheer up,\u201D they
        said. \u201CCome on, he\u2019s calling you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Bartimaeus threw aside his coat, jumped up, and came to Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CWhat do you want me to do for you?\u201D \n\tJesus asked.\n\t\u201CMy
        Rabbi,[COMMENT[0]]\u201D the blind man said, \u201CI want to see!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:51 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek uses the Hebrew term '
          body: Rabboni.
    - title: 
      content: "And Jesus said to him, \n\t\u201CGo, for your faith has healed you.\u201D
        Instantly the man could see, and he followed Jesus down the road.[COMMENT[0]]"
      comments:
      - number: '10:52 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: on the way.
  - verses:
    - title: "Jesus\u2019 Triumphant Entry"
      content: 'As Jesus and his disciples approached Jerusalem, they came to the
        towns of Bethphage and Bethany on the Mount of Olives. Jesus sent two of
        them on ahead. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo into that village over there,\u201D \n\the told them. \n\t\u201CAs
        soon as you enter it, you will see a young donkey tied there that no one
        has ever ridden. Untie it and bring it here.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If anyone asks, \u2018What are you doing?\u2019 just say, \u2018The
        Lord needs it and will return it soon.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The two disciples left and found the colt standing in the street,
        tied outside the front door. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As they were untying it, some bystanders demanded, \u201CWhat are
        you doing, untying that colt?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They said what Jesus had told them to say, and they were permitted
        to take it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then they brought the colt to Jesus and threw their garments over
        it, and he sat on it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Many in the crowd spread their garments on the road ahead of him,
        and others spread leafy branches they had cut in the fields. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus was in the center of the procession, and the people all around
        him were shouting,\n\t\u201CPraise God![COMMENT[0]]Blessings on the one who
        comes in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'Hosanna, '
        - ft: "an exclamation of praise that literally means \u201Csave now\u201D;
            also in 11:10."
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Blessings on the coming Kingdom of our ancestor David!\n\tPraise
        God in highest heaven!\u201D[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:9-10 '
        contents:
        - ft: Pss 118:25-26; 148:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'So Jesus came to Jerusalem and went into the Temple. After looking
        around carefully at everything, he left because it was late in the afternoon.
        Then he returned to Bethany with the twelve disciples.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Curses the Fig Tree
      content: 'The next morning as they were leaving Bethany, Jesus was hungry. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He noticed a fig tree in full leaf a little way off, so he went over
        to see if he could find any figs. But there were only leaves because it was
        too early in the season for fruit. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus said to the tree, \n\t\u201CMay no one ever eat your fruit
        again!\u201D And the disciples heard him say it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Clears the Temple
      content: 'When they arrived back in Jerusalem, Jesus entered the Temple and
        began to drive out the people buying and selling animals for sacrifices.
        He knocked over the tables of the money changers and the chairs of those
        selling doves, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and he stopped everyone from using the Temple as a marketplace.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: from carrying merchandise through the Temple.
    - title: 
      content: "He said to them, \n\t\u201CThe Scriptures declare, \u2018My Temple
        will be called a house of prayer for all nations,\u2019 but you have turned
        it into a den of thieves.\u201D[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: Isa 56:7; Jer 7:11.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'When the leading priests and teachers of religious law heard what
        Jesus had done, they began planning how to kill him. But they were afraid
        of him because the people were so amazed at his teaching.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That evening Jesus and the disciples left[COMMENT[0]] the city.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'they left; '
        - ft: 'other manuscripts read '
          body: he left.
    - title: 
      content: 'The next morning as they passed by the fig tree he had cursed, the
        disciples noticed it had withered from the roots up. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Peter remembered what Jesus had said to the tree on the previous
        day and exclaimed, \u201CLook, Rabbi! The fig tree you cursed has withered
        and died!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus said to the disciples, \n\t\u201CHave faith in God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I tell you the truth, you can say to this mountain, \u2018May you
        be lifted up and thrown into the sea,\u2019 and it will happen. But you must
        really believe it will happen and have no doubt in your heart.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I tell you, you can pray for anything, and if you believe that you\u2019ve
        received it, it will be yours.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But when you are praying, first forgive anyone you are holding a
        grudge against, so that your Father in heaven will forgive your sins, too.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:25 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts add verse 26, '
          body: 'But if you refuse to forgive, your Father in heaven will not forgive
            your sins. '
        - ft: Compare Matt 6:15.
          body: 
    - title: The Authority of Jesus Challenged
      content: 'Again they entered Jerusalem. As Jesus was walking through the Temple
        area, the leading priests, the teachers of religious law, and the elders
        came up to him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They demanded, \u201CBy what authority are you doing all these things?
        Who gave you the right to do them?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CI\u2019ll tell you by what authority I do these things
        if you answer one question,\u201D \n\tJesus replied. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDid John\u2019s authority to baptize come from heaven, or was
        it merely human? Answer me!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They talked it over among themselves. \u201CIf we say it was from
        heaven, he will ask why we didn\u2019t believe John. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But do we dare say it was merely human?\u201D For they were afraid
        of what the people would do, because everyone believed that John was a prophet. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So they finally replied, \u201CWe don\u2019t know.\u201D\n\tAnd Jesus
        responded, \n\t\u201CThen I won\u2019t tell you by what authority I do these
        things.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Parable of the Evil Farmers
      content: "Then Jesus began teaching them with stories: \n\t\u201CA man planted
        a vineyard. He built a wall around it, dug a pit for pressing out the grape
        juice, and built a lookout tower. Then he leased the vineyard to tenant farmers
        and moved to another country.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At the time of the grape harvest, he sent one of his servants to
        collect his share of the crop.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the farmers grabbed the servant, beat him up, and sent him back
        empty-handed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The owner then sent another servant, but they insulted him and beat
        him over the head.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The next servant he sent was killed. Others he sent were either beaten
        or killed,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "until there was only one left\u2014his son whom he loved dearly.
        The owner finally sent him, thinking, \u2018Surely they will respect my son.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CBut the tenant farmers said to one another, \u2018Here
        comes the heir to this estate. Let\u2019s kill him and get the estate for
        ourselves!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So they grabbed him and murdered him and threw his body out of the
        vineyard.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CWhat do you suppose the owner of the vineyard will do?\u201D
        \n\tJesus asked. \n\t\u201CI\u2019ll tell you\u2014he will come and kill
        those farmers and lease the vineyard to others.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Didn\u2019t you ever read this in the Scriptures?  \n\t\u2018The
        stone that the builders rejected  \n\thas now become the cornerstone.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\tThis is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s doing, 
        \n\tand it is wonderful to see.\u2019  [COMMENT[1]]  \n\t\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '12:10-11 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Ps 118:22-23.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The religious leaders[COMMENT[0]] wanted to arrest Jesus because
        they realized he was telling the story against them\u2014they were the wicked
        farmers. But they were afraid of the crowd, so they left him and went away.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: They.
    - title: Taxes for Caesar
      content: 'Later the leaders sent some Pharisees and supporters of Herod to
        trap Jesus into saying something for which he could be arrested. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTeacher,\u201D they said, \u201Cwe know how honest you are.
        You are impartial and don\u2019t play favorites. You teach the way of God
        truthfully. Now tell us\u2014is it right to pay taxes to Caesar or not? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Should we pay them, or shouldn\u2019t we?\u201D\n\tJesus saw through
        their hypocrisy and said, \n\t\u201CWhy are you trying to trap me? Show me
        a Roman coin,[COMMENT[0]]  \n\tand I\u2019ll tell you.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: a denarius.
    - title: 
      content: "When they handed it to him, he asked, \n\t\u201CWhose picture and
        title are stamped on it?\u201D\n\t\u201CCaesar\u2019s,\u201D they replied.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CWell, then,\u201D \n\tJesus said, \n\t\u201Cgive to Caesar
        what belongs to Caesar, and give to God what belongs to God.\u201D\n\tHis
        reply completely amazed them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Discussion about Resurrection
      content: "Then Jesus was approached by some Sadducees\u2014religious leaders
        who say there is no resurrection from the dead. They posed this question: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTeacher, Moses gave us a law that if a man dies, leaving a
        wife without children, his brother should marry the widow and have a child
        who will carry on the brother\u2019s name.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: See Deut 25:5-6.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Well, suppose there were seven brothers. The oldest one married and
        then died without children. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the second brother married the widow, but he also died without
        children. Then the third brother married her. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This continued with all seven of them, and still there were no children.
        Last of all, the woman also died. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So tell us, whose wife will she be in the resurrection? For all seven
        were married to her.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied, \n\t\u201CYour mistake is that you don\u2019t know
        the Scriptures, and you don\u2019t know the power of God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For when the dead rise, they will neither marry nor be given in marriage.
        In this respect they will be like the angels in heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CBut now, as to whether the dead will be raised\u2014haven\u2019t
        you ever read about this in the writings of Moses, in the story of the burning
        bush? Long after Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob had died, God said to Moses, 
        [COMMENT[1]]  \n\t\u2018I am the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the
        God of Jacob.\u2019[COMMENT[2]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '12:26a '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: in the story of the bush? God said to him.
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '12:26b '
        contents:
        - ft: Exod 3:6.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "So he is the God of the living, not the dead. You have made a serious
        error.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Most Important Commandment
      content: "One of the teachers of religious law was standing there listening
        to the debate. He realized that Jesus had answered well, so he asked, \u201COf
        all the commandments, which is the most important?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied, \n\t\u201CThe most important commandment is this:
        \u2018Listen, O Israel! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God is the one
        and only <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And you must love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God with all
        your heart, all your soul, all your mind, and all your strength.\u2019[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:29-30 '
        contents:
        - ft: Deut 6:4-5.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The second is equally important: \u2018Love your neighbor as yourself.\u2019[COMMENT[0]] 
        \n\tNo other commandment is greater than these.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:31 '
        contents:
        - ft: Lev 19:18.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The teacher of religious law replied, \u201CWell said, Teacher. You
        have spoken the truth by saying that there is only one God and no other. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I know it is important to love him with all my heart and all
        my understanding and all my strength, and to love my neighbor as myself.
        This is more important than to offer all of the burnt offerings and sacrifices
        required in the law.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Realizing how much the man understood, Jesus said to him, \n\t\u201CYou
        are not far from the Kingdom of God.\u201D And after that, no one dared to
        ask him any more questions.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Whose Son Is the Messiah?
      content: "Later, as Jesus was teaching the people in the Temple, he asked,
        \n\t\u201CWhy do the teachers of religious law claim that the Messiah is
        the son of David?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For David himself, speaking under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit,
        said,  \n\t\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to my Lord,  \n\tSit
        in the place of honor at my right hand  \n\tuntil I humble your enemies beneath
        your feet.\u2019  [COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '12:36 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Ps 110:1.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\tSince David himself called the Messiah \u2018my Lord,\u2019
        how can the Messiah be his son?\u201D The large crowd listened to him with
        great delight.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus also taught: \n\t\u201CBeware of these teachers of religious
        law! For they like to parade around in flowing robes and receive respectful
        greetings as they walk in the marketplaces.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And how they love the seats of honor in the synagogues and the head
        table at banquets.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet they shamelessly cheat widows out of their property and then
        pretend to be pious by making long prayers in public. Because of this, they
        will be more severely punished.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "The Widow\u2019s Offering"
      content: 'Jesus sat down near the collection box in the Temple and watched
        as the crowds dropped in their money. Many rich people put in large amounts. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then a poor widow came and dropped in two small coins.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:42 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'two lepta, which is a kodrantes '
        - ft: '[i.e., a quadrans].'
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus called his disciples to him and said, \n\t\u201CI tell you
        the truth, this poor widow has given more than all the others who are making
        contributions.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For they gave a tiny part of their surplus, but she, poor as she
        is, has given everything she had to live on.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jesus Speaks about the Future
      content: "As Jesus was leaving the Temple that day, one of his disciples said,
        \u201CTeacher, look at these magnificent buildings! Look at the impressive
        stones in the walls.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied, \n\t\u201CYes, look at these great buildings. But
        they will be completely demolished. Not one stone will be left on top of
        another!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Later, Jesus sat on the Mount of Olives across the valley from the
        Temple. Peter, James, John, and Andrew came to him privately and asked him, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTell us, when will all this happen? What sign will show us
        that these things are about to be fulfilled?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied, \n\t\u201CDon\u2019t let anyone mislead you,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for many will come in my name, claiming, \u2018I am the Messiah.\u2019[COMMENT[0]] 
        \n\tThey will deceive many.  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: "claiming, \u2018I am.\u2019"
    - title: 
      content: "And you will hear of wars and threats of wars, but don\u2019t panic.
        Yes, these things must take place, but the end won\u2019t follow immediately.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Nation will go to war against nation, and kingdom against kingdom.
        There will be earthquakes in many parts of the world, as well as famines.
        But this is only the first of the birth pains, with more to come.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CWhen these things begin to happen, watch out! You will
        be handed over to the local councils and beaten in the synagogues. You will
        stand trial before governors and kings because you are my followers. But
        this will be your opportunity to tell them about me.  [COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '13:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: But this will be your testimony against them.
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'For the Good News must first be preached to all nations.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: all peoples.
    - title: 
      content: "But when you are arrested and stand trial, don\u2019t worry in advance
        about what to say. Just say what God tells you at that time, for it is not
        you who will be speaking, but the Holy Spirit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CA brother will betray his brother to death, a father
        will betray his own child, and children will rebel against their parents
        and cause them to be killed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And everyone will hate you because you are my followers.[COMMENT[0]] 
        \n\tBut the one who endures to the end will be saved.  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: on account of my name.
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CThe day is coming when you will see the sacrilegious
        object that causes desecration  [COMMENT[1]]  \n\tstanding where he[COMMENT[2]] 
        \n\tshould not be.\u201D (Reader, pay attention!) \n\t\u201CThen those in
        Judea must flee to the hills.  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
