          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '13:14b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: it.
    - title: 
      content: 'A person out on the deck of a roof must not go down into the house
        to pack.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A person out in the field must not return even to get a coat.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How terrible it will be for pregnant women and for nursing mothers
        in those days.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And pray that your flight will not be in winter.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For there will be greater anguish in those days than at any time
        since God created the world. And it will never be so great again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In fact, unless the Lord shortens that time of calamity, not a single
        person will survive. But for the sake of his chosen ones he has shortened
        those days.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CThen if anyone tells you, \u2018Look, here is the Messiah,\u2019
        or \u2018There he is,\u2019 don\u2019t believe it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For false messiahs and false prophets will rise up and perform signs
        and wonders so as to deceive, if possible, even God\u2019s chosen ones.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Watch out! I have warned you about this ahead of time!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CAt that time, after the anguish of those days,  \n\tthe
        sun will be darkened,  \n\tthe moon will give no light,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\tthe stars will fall from the sky,  \n\tand the powers in the
        heavens will be shaken.  [COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '13:24-25 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: See Isa 13:10; 34:4; Joel 2:10.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\tThen everyone will see the Son of Man  [COMMENT[1]]  \n\tcoming
        on the clouds with great power and glory.[COMMENT[2]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '13:26a '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '13:26b '
        contents:
        - ft: See Dan 7:13.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "And he will send out his angels to gather his chosen ones from all
        over the world[COMMENT[0]]\u2014from the farthest ends of the earth and heaven.  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:27 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: from the four winds.
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CNow learn a lesson from the fig tree. When its branches
        bud and its leaves begin to sprout, you know that summer is near.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the same way, when you see all these things taking place, you
        can know that his return is very near, right at the door.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I tell you the truth, this generation[COMMENT[0]]  \n\twill not pass
        from the scene before all these things take place.  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:30 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'this age, '
        - ft: 'or '
          body: this nation.
    - title: 
      content: 'Heaven and earth will disappear, but my words will never disappear.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CHowever, no one knows the day or hour when these things
        will happen, not even the angels in heaven or the Son himself. Only the Father
        knows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And since you don\u2019t know when that time will come, be on guard!
        Stay alert[COMMENT[0]]!  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:33 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts add '
          body: and pray.
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\t\u201CThe coming of the Son of Man can be illustrated by the
        story of a man going on a long trip. When he left home, he gave each of his
        slaves instructions about the work they were to do, and he told the gatekeeper
        to watch for his return.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You, too, must keep watch! For you don\u2019t know when the master
        of the household will return\u2014in the evening, at midnight, before dawn,
        or at daybreak.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let him find you sleeping when he arrives without warning.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I say to you what I say to everyone: Watch for him!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jesus Anointed at Bethany
      content: 'It was now two days before Passover and the Festival of Unleavened
        Bread. The leading priests and the teachers of religious law were still looking
        for an opportunity to capture Jesus secretly and kill him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut not during the Passover celebration,\u201D they agreed,
        \u201Cor the people may riot.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Meanwhile, Jesus was in Bethany at the home of Simon, a man who had
        previously had leprosy. While he was eating,[COMMENT[0]] a woman came in
        with a beautiful alabaster jar of expensive perfume made from essence of
        nard. She broke open the jar and poured the perfume over his head.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: reclining.
    - title: 
      content: "Some of those at the table were indignant. \u201CWhy waste such expensive
        perfume?\u201D they asked. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIt could have been sold for a year\u2019s wages[COMMENT[0]]
        and the money given to the poor!\u201D So they scolded her harshly.  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'for 300 denarii. '
        - ft: "A denarius was equivalent to a laborer\u2019s full day\u2019s wage."
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus replied, \n\t\u201CLeave her alone. Why criticize her for
        doing such a good thing to me?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will always have the poor among you, and you can help them whenever
        you want to. But you will not always have me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She has done what she could and has anointed my body for burial ahead
        of time.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I tell you the truth, wherever the Good News is preached throughout
        the world, this woman\u2019s deed will be remembered and discussed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Judas Agrees to Betray Jesus
      content: 'Then Judas Iscariot, one of the twelve disciples, went to the leading
        priests to arrange to betray Jesus to them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were delighted when they heard why he had come, and they promised
        to give him money. So he began looking for an opportunity to betray Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Last Supper
      content: "On the first day of the Festival of Unleavened Bread, when the Passover
        lamb is sacrificed, Jesus\u2019 disciples asked him, \u201CWhere do you want
        us to go to prepare the Passover meal for you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Jesus sent two of them into Jerusalem with these instructions:
        \n\t\u201CAs you go into the city, a man carrying a pitcher of water will
        meet you. Follow him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At the house he enters, say to the owner, \u2018The Teacher asks:
        Where is the guest room where I can eat the Passover meal with my disciples?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will take you upstairs to a large room that is already set up.
        That is where you should prepare our meal.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the two disciples went into the city and found everything just
        as Jesus had said, and they prepared the Passover meal there.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the evening Jesus arrived with the Twelve. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As they were at the table[COMMENT[0]] eating, Jesus said, \n\t\u201CI
        tell you the truth, one of you eating with me here will betray me.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: As they reclined.
    - title: 
      content: "Greatly distressed, each one asked in turn, \u201CAm I the one?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He replied, \n\t\u201CIt is one of you twelve who is eating from
        this bowl with me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the Son of Man[COMMENT[0]]  \n\tmust die, as the Scriptures declared
        long ago. But how terrible it will be for the one who betrays him. It would
        be far better for that man if he had never been born!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "As they were eating, Jesus took some bread and blessed it. Then he
        broke it in pieces and gave it to the disciples, saying, \n\t\u201CTake it,
        for this is my body.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And he took a cup of wine and gave thanks to God for it. He gave
        it to them, and they all drank from it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he said to them, \n\t\u201CThis is my blood, which confirms the
        covenant[COMMENT[0]]  \n\tbetween God and his people. It is poured out as
        a sacrifice for many.  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:24 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts read '
          body: the new covenant.
    - title: 
      content: "I tell you the truth, I will not drink wine again until the day I
        drink it new in the Kingdom of God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then they sang a hymn and went out to the Mount of Olives.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "Jesus Predicts Peter\u2019s Denial"
      content: "On the way, Jesus told them, \n\t\u201CAll of you will desert me.
        For the Scriptures say,  \n\t\u2018God will strike  [COMMENT[1]]  \n\tthe
        Shepherd,  \n\tand the sheep will be scattered.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '14:27 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 'I will strike. '
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Zech 13:7.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "  \n\tBut after I am raised from the dead, I will go ahead of you
        to Galilee and meet you there.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Peter said to him, \u201CEven if everyone else deserts you, I never
        will.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied, \n\t\u201CI tell you the truth, Peter\u2014this very
        night, before the rooster crows twice, you will deny three times that you
        even know me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNo!\u201D Peter declared emphatically. \u201CEven if I have
        to die with you, I will never deny you!\u201D And all the others vowed the
        same.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Prays in Gethsemane
      content: "They went to the olive grove called Gethsemane, and Jesus said, \n\t\u201CSit
        here while I go and pray.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He took Peter, James, and John with him, and he became deeply troubled
        and distressed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He told them, \n\t\u201CMy soul is crushed with grief to the point
        of death. Stay here and keep watch with me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He went on a little farther and fell to the ground. He prayed that,
        if it were possible, the awful hour awaiting him might pass him by. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAbba, Father,\u201D[COMMENT[0]] he cried out, \n\t\u201Ceverything
        is possible for you. Please take this cup of suffering away from me. Yet
        I want your will to be done, not mine.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:36 '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Abba '
        - ft: "is an Aramaic term for \u201Cfather.\u201D"
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Then he returned and found the disciples asleep. He said to Peter,
        \n\t\u201CSimon, are you asleep? Couldn\u2019t you watch with me even one
        hour?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Keep watch and pray, so that you will not give in to temptation.
        For the spirit is willing, but the body is weak.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Jesus left them again and prayed the same prayer as before. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When he returned to them again, he found them sleeping, for they
        couldn\u2019t keep their eyes open. And they didn\u2019t know what to say.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When he returned to them the third time, he said, \n\t\u201CGo ahead
        and sleep. Have your rest. But no\u2014the time has come. The Son of Man
        is betrayed into the hands of sinners.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Up, let\u2019s be going. Look, my betrayer is here!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Is Betrayed and Arrested
      content: 'And immediately, even as Jesus said this, Judas, one of the twelve
        disciples, arrived with a crowd of men armed with swords and clubs. They
        had been sent by the leading priests, the teachers of religious law, and
        the elders. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The traitor, Judas, had given them a prearranged signal: \u201CYou
        will know which one to arrest when I greet him with a kiss. Then you can
        take him away under guard.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As soon as they arrived, Judas walked up to Jesus. \u201CRabbi!\u201D
        he exclaimed, and gave him the kiss.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the others grabbed Jesus and arrested him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But one of the men with Jesus pulled out his sword and struck the
        high priest\u2019s slave, slashing off his ear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus asked them, \n\t\u201CAm I some dangerous revolutionary, that
        you come with swords and clubs to arrest me?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why didn\u2019t you arrest me in the Temple? I was there among you
        teaching every day. But these things are happening to fulfill what the Scriptures
        say about me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then all his disciples deserted him and ran away. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'One young man following behind was clothed only in a long linen shirt.
        When the mob tried to grab him, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'he slipped out of his shirt and ran away naked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus before the Council
      content: "They took Jesus to the high priest\u2019s home where the leading
        priests, the elders, and the teachers of religious law had gathered. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Meanwhile, Peter followed him at a distance and went right into the
        high priest\u2019s courtyard. There he sat with the guards, warming himself
        by the fire.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Inside, the leading priests and the entire high council[COMMENT[0]]
        were trying to find evidence against Jesus, so they could put him to death.
        But they couldn\u2019t find any. "
      comments:
      - number: '14:55 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: the Sanhedrin.
    - title: 
      content: 'Many false witnesses spoke against him, but they contradicted each
        other. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Finally, some men stood up and gave this false testimony: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWe heard him say, \u2018I will destroy this Temple made with
        human hands, and in three days I will build another, made without human hands.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But even then they didn\u2019t get their stories straight!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the high priest stood up before the others and asked Jesus,
        \u201CWell, aren\u2019t you going to answer these charges? What do you have
        to say for yourself?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus was silent and made no reply. Then the high priest asked
        him, \u201CAre you the Messiah, the Son of the Blessed One?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus said, \n\t\u201C<smallcaps>I Am</smallcaps>\n\t.[COMMENT[0]] 
        \n\tAnd you will see the Son of Man seated in the place of power at God\u2019s
        right hand[COMMENT[1]]  \n\tand coming on the clouds of heaven.[COMMENT[2]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:62a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: "The \u2018"
        - ft: 'or '
          body: 'I am the '
        - ft: See Exod 3:14.
          body: 
      - number: '14:62b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'seated at the right hand of the power. '
        - ft: See Ps 110:1.
          body: 
      - number: '14:62c '
        contents:
        - ft: See Dan 7:13.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Then the high priest tore his clothing to show his horror and said,
        \u201CWhy do we need other witnesses? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have all heard his blasphemy. What is your verdict?\u201D\n\t\u201CGuilty!\u201D
        they all cried. \u201CHe deserves to die!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then some of them began to spit at him, and they blindfolded him
        and beat him with their fists. \u201CProphesy to us,\u201D they jeered. And
        the guards slapped him as they took him away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Peter Denies Jesus
      content: 'Meanwhile, Peter was in the courtyard below. One of the servant girls
        who worked for the high priest came by '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and noticed Peter warming himself at the fire. She looked at him
        closely and said, \u201CYou were one of those with Jesus of Nazareth.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:67 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Jesus the Nazarene.
    - title: 
      content: "But Peter denied it. \u201CI don\u2019t know what you\u2019re talking
        about,\u201D he said, and he went out into the entryway. Just then, a rooster
        crowed.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:68 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts do not include '
          body: Just then, a rooster crowed.
    - title: 
      content: "When the servant girl saw him standing there, she began telling the
        others, \u201CThis man is definitely one of them!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Peter denied it again.\n\tA little later some of the other bystanders
        confronted Peter and said, \u201CYou must be one of them, because you are
        a Galilean.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Peter swore, \u201CA curse on me if I\u2019m lying\u2014I don\u2019t
        know this man you\u2019re talking about!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And immediately the rooster crowed the second time.\n\tSuddenly,
        Jesus\u2019 words flashed through Peter\u2019s mind: \n\t\u201CBefore the
        rooster crows twice, you will deny three times that you even know me.\u201D
        And he broke down and wept."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Jesus\u2019 Trial before Pilate"
      content: "Very early in the morning the leading priests, the elders, and the
        teachers of religious law\u2014the entire high council[COMMENT[0]]\u2014met
        to discuss their next step. They bound Jesus, led him away, and took him
        to Pilate, the Roman governor.  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'the Sanhedrin; '
        - ft: also in 15:43.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Pilate asked Jesus, \u201CAre you the king of the Jews?\u201D\n\tJesus
        replied, \n\t\u201CYou have said it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the leading priests kept accusing him of many crimes, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and Pilate asked him, \u201CAren\u2019t you going to answer them?
        What about all these charges they are bringing against you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus said nothing, much to Pilate\u2019s surprise.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now it was the governor\u2019s custom each year during the Passover
        celebration to release one prisoner\u2014anyone the people requested. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'One of the prisoners at that time was Barabbas, a revolutionary who
        had committed murder in an uprising. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The crowd went to Pilate and asked him to release a prisoner as usual.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWould you like me to release to you this \u2018King of the
        Jews\u2019?\u201D Pilate asked. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(For he realized by now that the leading priests had arrested Jesus
        out of envy.) '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But at this point the leading priests stirred up the crowd to demand
        the release of Barabbas instead of Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Pilate asked them, \u201CThen what should I do with this man you
        call the king of the Jews?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They shouted back, \u201CCrucify him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhy?\u201D Pilate demanded. \u201CWhat crime has he committed?\u201D\n\tBut
        the mob roared even louder, \u201CCrucify him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So to pacify the crowd, Pilate released Barabbas to them. He ordered
        Jesus flogged with a lead-tipped whip, then turned him over to the Roman
        soldiers to be crucified.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Soldiers Mock Jesus
      content: "The soldiers took Jesus into the courtyard of the governor\u2019s
        headquarters (called the Praetorium) and called out the entire regiment. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They dressed him in a purple robe, and they wove thorn branches into
        a crown and put it on his head. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they saluted him and taunted, \u201CHail! King of the Jews!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And they struck him on the head with a reed stick, spit on him, and
        dropped to their knees in mock worship. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they were finally tired of mocking him, they took off the purple
        robe and put his own clothes on him again. Then they led him away to be crucified.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Crucifixion
      content: "A passerby named Simon, who was from Cyrene,[COMMENT[0]] was coming
        in from the countryside just then, and the soldiers forced him to carry Jesus\u2019
        cross. (Simon was the father of Alexander and Rufus.) "
      comments:
      - number: '15:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Cyrene '
        - ft: was a city in northern Africa.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "And they brought Jesus to a place called Golgotha (which means \u201CPlace
        of the Skull\u201D). "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They offered him wine drugged with myrrh, but he refused it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the soldiers nailed him to the cross. They divided his clothes
        and threw dice[COMMENT[0]] to decide who would get each piece. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:24 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'cast lots. '
        - ft: See Ps 22:18.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "It was nine o\u2019clock in the morning when they crucified him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A sign announced the charge against him. It read, \u201CThe King
        of the Jews.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Two revolutionaries[COMMENT[0]] were crucified with him, one on his
        right and one on his left.[COMMENT[1]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:27a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Two criminals.
      - number: '15:27b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts add verse 28, '
          body: "And the Scripture was fulfilled that said, \u201CHe was counted
            among those who were rebels.\u201D "
        - ft: See Isa 53:12; also compare Luke 22:37.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The people passing by shouted abuse, shaking their heads in mockery.
        \u201CHa! Look at you now!\u201D they yelled at him. \u201CYou said you were
        going to destroy the Temple and rebuild it in three days. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Well then, save yourself and come down from the cross!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The leading priests and teachers of religious law also mocked Jesus.
        \u201CHe saved others,\u201D they scoffed, \u201Cbut he can\u2019t save himself! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let this Messiah, this King of Israel, come down from the cross so
        we can see it and believe him!\u201D Even the men who were crucified with
        Jesus ridiculed him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Death of Jesus
      content: "At noon, darkness fell across the whole land until three o\u2019clock. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then at three o\u2019clock Jesus called out with a loud voice, \n\t\u201CEloi,
        Eloi, lema sabachthani?\u201D which means \n\t\u201CMy God, my God, why have
        you abandoned me?\u201D[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:34 '
        contents:
        - ft: Ps 22:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Some of the bystanders misunderstood and thought he was calling for
        the prophet Elijah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One of them ran and filled a sponge with sour wine, holding it up
        to him on a reed stick so he could drink. \u201CWait!\u201D he said. \u201CLet\u2019s
        see whether Elijah comes to take him down!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Jesus uttered another loud cry and breathed his last. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the curtain in the sanctuary of the Temple was torn in two, from
        top to bottom.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the Roman officer[COMMENT[0]] who stood facing him[COMMENT[1]]
        saw how he had died, he exclaimed, \u201CThis man truly was the Son of God!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:39a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'the centurion; '
        - ft: similarly in 15:44, 45.
          body: 
      - number: '15:39b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts add '
          body: heard his cry and.
    - title: 
      content: 'Some women were there, watching from a distance, including Mary Magdalene,
        Mary (the mother of James the younger and of Joseph[COMMENT[0]]), and Salome. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:40 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'Joses; '
        - ft: also in 15:47. See Matt 27:56.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'They had been followers of Jesus and had cared for him while he was
        in Galilee. Many other women who had come with him to Jerusalem were also
        there.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Burial of Jesus
      content: 'This all happened on Friday, the day of preparation,[COMMENT[0]]
        the day before the Sabbath. As evening approached, '
      comments:
      - number: '15:42 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: It was the day of preparation.
    - title: 
      content: "Joseph of Arimathea took a risk and went to Pilate and asked for
        Jesus\u2019 body. (Joseph was an honored member of the high council, and
        he was waiting for the Kingdom of God to come.) "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Pilate couldn\u2019t believe that Jesus was already dead, so he called
        for the Roman officer and asked if he had died yet. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The officer confirmed that Jesus was dead, so Pilate told Joseph
        he could have the body. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Joseph bought a long sheet of linen cloth. Then he took Jesus\u2019
        body down from the cross, wrapped it in the cloth, and laid it in a tomb
        that had been carved out of the rock. Then he rolled a stone in front of
        the entrance. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joseph saw where Jesus\u2019
        body was laid."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Resurrection
      content: "Saturday evening, when the Sabbath ended, Mary Magdalene, Mary the
        mother of James, and Salome went out and purchased burial spices so they
        could anoint Jesus\u2019 body. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Very early on Sunday morning,[COMMENT[0]] just at sunrise, they went
        to the tomb. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'on the first day of the week; '
        - ft: also in 16:9.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "On the way they were asking each other, \u201CWho will roll away
        the stone for us from the entrance to the tomb?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But as they arrived, they looked up and saw that the stone, which
        was very large, had already been rolled aside.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they entered the tomb, they saw a young man clothed in a white
        robe sitting on the right side. The women were shocked, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but the angel said, \u201CDon\u2019t be alarmed. You are looking
        for Jesus of Nazareth,[COMMENT[0]] who was crucified. He isn\u2019t here!
        He is risen from the dead! Look, this is where they laid his body. "
      comments:
      - number: '16:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Jesus the Nazarene.
    - title: 
      content: "Now go and tell his disciples, including Peter, that Jesus is going
        ahead of you to Galilee. You will see him there, just as he told you before
        he died.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The women fled from the tomb, trembling and bewildered, and they
        said nothing to anyone because they were too frightened.[COMMENT[0]]----------\n\t[\n\tThe
        most ancient manuscripts of Mark conclude with verse 16:8. Later manuscripts
        add one or both of the following endings.\n\t]\n\t[\n\tShorter Ending of
        Mark\n\t]\n\tThen they briefly reported all this to Peter and his companions.
        Afterward Jesus himself sent them out from east to west with the sacred and
        unfailing message of salvation that gives eternal life. Amen.\n\t[\n\tLonger
        Ending of Mark\n\t]  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: "The most reliable early manuscripts of the Gospel of Mark end at verse
            8. Other manuscripts include various endings to the Gospel. A few include
            both the \u201Cshorter ending\u201D and the \u201Clonger ending.\u201D
            The majority of manuscripts include the \u201Clonger ending\u201D immediately
            after verse 8."
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'After Jesus rose from the dead early on Sunday morning, the first
        person who saw him was Mary Magdalene, the woman from whom he had cast out
        seven demons. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She went to the disciples, who were grieving and weeping, and told
        them what had happened. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But when she told them that Jesus was alive and she had seen him,
        they didn\u2019t believe her.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Afterward he appeared in a different form to two of his followers
        who were walking from Jerusalem into the country. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They rushed back to tell the others, but no one believed them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Still later he appeared to the eleven disciples as they were eating
        together. He rebuked them for their stubborn unbelief because they refused
        to believe those who had seen him after he had been raised from the dead.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some early manuscripts add: '
          body: "And they excused themselves, saying, \u201CThis age of lawlessness
            and unbelief is under Satan, who does not permit God\u2019s truth and
            power to conquer the evil [unclean] spirits. Therefore, reveal your justice
            now.\u201D This is what they said to Christ. And Christ replied to them,
            \u201CThe period of years of Satan\u2019s power has been fulfilled, but
            other dreadful things will happen soon. And I was handed over to death
            for those who have sinned, so that they may return to the truth and sin
            no more, and so they may inherit the spiritual, incorruptible, and righteous
            glory in heaven.\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: "And then he told them, \n\t\u201CGo into all the world and preach
        the Good News to everyone.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Anyone who believes and is baptized will be saved. But anyone who
        refuses to believe will be condemned.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These miraculous signs will accompany those who believe: They will
        cast out demons in my name, and they will speak in new languages.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'new tongues; '
        - ft: 'some manuscripts do not include '
          body: new.
    - title: 
      content: "They will be able to handle snakes with safety, and if they drink
        anything poisonous, it won\u2019t hurt them. They will be able to place their
        hands on the sick, and they will be healed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the Lord Jesus had finished talking with them, he was taken
        up into heaven and sat down in the place of honor at God\u2019s right hand. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: And the disciples went everywhere and preached, and the Lord worked
        through them, confirming what they said by many miraculous signs.
      comments: []
